claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: A tabular listing of influenza vaccines (standard-dose egg-based, standard-dose cell culture-based, and high-dose egg-based) showing vaccine names, presentations, age indications, HA antigen content per dose (e.g., 15 µg/0.5 mL for standard-dose, 60 µg/0.7 mL for high-dose), route of administration, and thimerosal content. The table does not include Flublok or its HA content, and therefore does not support the claim regarding Flublok containing 3× the HA antigen of standard-dose vaccines; it doesn’t support the claim. Note: Image shows only part of a multi-page table; Flublok may appear elsewhere but is not visible here.
